{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 1032 (PR #3422) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3422.","id":"vf_4ab995df9d3e9b5b","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Improved partial result (Lean).","id":"vf_7abf8d59a73aa7e6","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1032: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. We say that a graph is $4$-chromatic critical if it has chromatic number $4$, and removing any edge decreases the chromatic number to $3$.\n\nIs there, for arbitrarily large $n$, a $4$-chromatic critical graph on $n$ vertices with minimum degree $\\gg n$? Current best: Toft conjectured that a $4$-chromatic critical graph on $n$ vertices has at least $(\\frac{5}{3}+o(1))n$ vertices, and has examples to show this would be the best possible. Prize: no. Tags: chromatic number, graph theory.","id":"vf_91131c974ee815e2","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1032.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_4ab995df9d3e9b5b","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:1032","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_4ab995df9d3e9b5b","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_91131c974ee815e2","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_7abf8d59a73aa7e6","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d0